SIMPLE: sightless
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sightless
<hw>Sight"less</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Lacking sight;
without sight; blind.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Of all who blindly creep or <qex>sightless</qex> soar.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That can not be seen; invisible.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>sightless</qex> couriers of the air.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Offensive or unpleasing to the eye; unsightly;
<as>as, <ex>sightless</ex> stains</as>.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Sight"less*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos>-
<wf>Sight"less*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sightliness</ent>⟦br⟧
